@LoginAPI_HostAddress = http://localhost:5177

### Register a new user
POST {{LoginAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "Test@1234",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

###

### Register another user
POST {{LoginAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass@123",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith"
}

###

### Login with registered user
POST {{LoginAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "Test@1234"
}

###

### Login with wrong password (should fail)
POST {{LoginAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword123"
}

###

### Get current user details (requires valid JWT token)
### Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN with the token from login response
GET {{LoginAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

